// smplOS default VS Code keybindings.
//
// Copied to ~/.config/Code/User/keybindings.json for new users at install
// time and by the 20260724-* migration for existing users (only if they
// don't already have keybindings.json — user customisations are never
// overwritten).
//
// ── Ctrl+Alt+C — focus GitHub Copilot Chat input ────────────────────────────
// Companion to the smplos black-screen recovery workflow: when the nvidia+
// Hyprland DPMS bug leaves the display dark, the user can hit Ctrl+Alt+C
// blindly (assuming VS Code is the focused window — usually true during
// coding sessions), start typing, and hit Enter to send. The chat input
// receives keystrokes even when the compositor isn't drawing, so the
// message reaches the assistant and we can diagnose without a hard reboot.
//
// The compositor-level Ctrl+Alt+C binding in Hyprland's emergency.conf was
// intentionally REMOVED so VS Code sees this keypress. If the compositor
// grabbed it, VS Code would never fire this rule.
[
    {
        "key": "ctrl+alt+c",
        "command": "workbench.action.chat.open",
        "when": "chatIsEnabled"
    }
]
